KYZJ WLETKZFE VOVTLKVJ TFUV KYRK KRBVJ JKRKZT JKIZEX ZEGLK REU UVTIZGJ KYIFLXY IFKRKZFE DVKYFU. R BEFNE GIFSCVD ZJ KYRK ZK RJJLDVJ JKREURIU VEXCZJY ZJ LJVU MZR RJJLDZEX V KF SV KYV DFJK, FI JVTFEU DFJK TFDDFE TYRI. KYZJ ZJ EFK RCNRPJ KYV TRJV V.X: SVEARDZE PFLEX YRJ E RJ KYV DFJK TFDDFE TYRI. Z YRMV UVTZUVU EFK KF 'SILKV' WFITV KYZJ, NYZTY NZCC IVJLCK ZE KYV GIZEKZEX FW 26 KVOK JVKJ, REU KRTBCVU KYV GIFSCVD NZKY KYV DVKYFU RSFMV.A standard alphabet char array is used. Returns Nothing
qwertyuiopasdfghjklzxcvbnm
abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz
//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Above data needs to be formated as follows:
1   #[ROTATION KEY]
2   [TEXT TO BE TRANSLATED]
3   [SUBSTITUTION KEY]
4   abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz

Menu options:
-Rotation:
    Enter (1) to encript message
    Enter (2) to decript message
-Substitution:
    Enter (3) to encript message
    Enter (4) to decript message

Rotation Key:
-Can be any integer. Will be moded by 26 and made positive

Substitution key:
-The substitution key needs to be exactly 26 characted long, can be upper or lowercase.
-Should include one of every character in the alfabet, and no spaces.
-Characters replace respective characters of standard alphabetical order.

Cipher text:
-The cipher text can be upto 10,000 charactes long, and can be upper or lower case.
-Will always be printed in uppercase
-Can not have [ENTER], must be on one line

OUTPUT:
-Printed in file Output and on terminal







